Check you you arlready have one pair in your linux syste.
 
$ ls -al ~/.ssh
# Lists the files in your .ssh directory, if they ex

if not pair if public and private key exist then

$ ssh-keygen
Enter file in which to save the key (/home/your_user/.ssh/id_rsa): <Enter>
Enter passphrase (empty for no passphrase): <Enter>
Enter same passphrase again: <Enter>
Your identification has been saved..


-----

Add your public key into the Git Repo

identify the new public key generated 
ls -al ~/.ssh

and copy to the clipboard the public one

cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub


Open your repo URL and find your profile / Setting SSH and add it

The steps are in the following link
https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/adding-a-new-ssh-key-to-your-github-account

